.TH VEK_COSINE_B1 3 "2024-01-01" "vek 0.8.0" "Library Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
vek_cosine_b1 \- cosine similarity for binary vectors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <vek.h>
.sp
.BI "float vek_cosine_b1(const uint8_t *" a ", const uint8_t *" b ", size_t " n ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR vek_cosine_b1 ()
computes the cosine similarity between two binary vectors packed into uint8
arrays:
.PP
.RS
result = dot_b1(a, b) / (popcount(a) * popcount(b))
.RE
.PP
The result ranges from 0.0 (disjoint) to 1.0 (identical). Since binary
vectors are non-negative, cosine similarity cannot be negative. If either
vector is all zeros, the result is undefined.
.SH PARAMETERS
.TP
.I a
First input binary vector packed into uint8 bytes. Must have at least
.I n
elements.
.TP
.I b
Second input binary vector packed into uint8 bytes. Must have at least
.I n
elements.
.TP
.I n
Number of uint8 elements (not bits). Must be greater than 0.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the cosine similarity as a single-precision float in the range
[0.0, 1.0].
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
uint8_t a[] = {0xFF, 0x0F};  // 11111111 00001111
uint8_t b[] = {0xFF, 0xFF};  // 11111111 11111111
float result = vek_cosine_b1(a, b, 2);  // 0.8
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vek_dot_b1 (3),
.BR vek_hamming_b1 (3),
.BR vek_cosine_u8 (3)
